rComments: Fantastic lecturer, super passionate and knowledgeable about the material. Even though I wasn't into Italian Opera, but she made them enjoyable! So sad it's her last year teaching

She's a decent person, but not a very good professor. She refuses to use portal, and instead uses an alternate site which requires a login that she gives you in the first lecture. Everything you need for the course is on this website, so if you find yourself unable to log in--tough luck! Won't be able to do anything else except email her for help.
Very enthusiastic and approachable prof!

People who rate her low are most likely performance majors who couldn't give a rat's ass about academic subjects and actively hate doing any written work in any form. Professor Parker is an amazing lecturer, very clear in her explanations, and a fantastic keyboard player. Probably my favourite course in first year.

Really interesting lectures which she usually ended early. Tests were pure memorization, but manageable. Really passionate about what she was teaching, even brought in her personal harpsichord and played it for the class. Readings were super short and relevant. A really fun, interesting class, very easy to do well.

Worst professor ever. Not understanding or helpful at all. Tests are contradicting to what she says in class and you ask her about a question missed and she says that could be right but it's not. She did not show up to one of the tests and then tried to tell us that if we have questions on a test we could have asked her but she wasn't even there
She is a space cadet. Can't operate the A/V equipment, much less her own laptop.. She seemed very disorganized but didn't lack qualification in the material taught.
Though a very sweet woman, I found that she was a rather tough marker who contradicted her shared expectations of course material.

A dull lecturer who relied heavily on video clips from documentaries.  However, was very understanding when I was unable to attend the final exam and made provisions for me.  Assignments were unclear as to what she wanted from us, but grading was fairly lenient. All in all, the definition of a mixed bag.  Meh.

This prof and course were a mixed bag. She relied far too heavily on the course readings during lectures, and would often show long video excerpts instead of teaching on her own. The essays were unclear, and the tests seemed to be graded harshly. For someone who is very interested in 60s music this was a bit of a disappointment.
She's just awesome.

Don't place much faith in negative comments expressed in these ratings. People who can't spell shouldn't be in university and no wonder they get bad marks in her class.  How about doing a little more  studying and less time badmouthing excellent profs?

Totally engaging, loves the material she is teaching.  Her enthusiasm is infectious. Encourages an imaginative approach to assignments,  is fair but no pushover.  Returns tests and assignments when promised.  I'd take a course again with her, in a heartbeat.
Good and helpful professor, teaches material in a clear way, but way too much work for a half year course, 2 essays and 2 tests...tests are fair
One of the best profs I've ever had.

She is very spacey and she relied too heavily on A/V material. She was always wigged-out and frustrated with the A/V equipment, which only demonstrated her incompetence. Her office hours were ephemeral and only convenienced her. The term tests, marked by the TAs, were marked too hard for a 50-minute test. An unfortunate university experience.
Best prof ever! Interesting, explains well and very helpful.
she keeps your attention AND always talks about relevant information; you know what will be required for tests/papers
I thought Prof Parker was great. She was interesting, enthusiastic and approachable. She really made the class enjoyable. I loved having her as a prof.

I don't know why so many of these posts are down on Prof. Parker. She was a very good teacher, very nice, very enthusiastic, and very accessible. She even repeated an entire lecture, in her office, for me and this other guy who'd missed it. She played the piano, played CD's for us, lectured us for one hour. Most helpful Professor ever. Thank-you!

Likes to go on long pointless rantings and focuses too much on form analysis rather than historical/biographical events. Overall a disappointment. Didn't really teach anything of value, but exposed us to some great music. HOWEVER, if you're good at listening tests you can expect nothing more than to totally kick ass in this course. *thumbs up*

Interesting prof. She has valuable insight into the pieces we studied, the composers and the eras as well. She tends to be a little flighty at times, but her digressions are at least interesting. She manages the class well, but at times it seems condescending towards students involved. Doesn't like *anyone* talking but her.

Prof. Parker is enthousiastic and obviously knows her material inside and out.  She is a music historian, and I felt that came through in the lectures.  The reading material that is assigned is pretty much useless, but it is a great class overall.

another case of "why the F$%# am I paying for this?"her lectures were boring, unispired lifts from the readings, and the only original bits were nostalgic musings about her youth-sorry, but i dont really care.take it as a blow off course, but dont expect to learn much about music in the '60's
Obviously very enthusiastic about what she teaches. A very fun class, but at some points she tended to just read aloud from assigned readings. Regardless, I would take any of her other classes.
music of the 1960s. really good material, but somehow she seems to make it hard
No Comments
No Comments
Great Instructor, and the tests are very fair.  she is very interested in what she teaches which makes the lectures even more interesting.

Prof. Parker is one of the most enthusiastic profs at that music faculty.  Other music profs should follow her example.  Her lectures are always interesting, her tests are fair, and her enthusiasm for music history is contagious.
Enthusiastic, smart, and funny.  Doesn't take any chatter or whispering during class.  Good for her!
I really, truly, think she is insane.  She flies off the handle and humiliates students and then laughs about it.  A dangerous person.
